---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHead from '../components/PageHead.astro';
import Pillar from '../components/Pillar.astro';
import CTABand from '../components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Octopad | Human-AI symbiosis for small teams"
  description="Why we built Octopad: the shared backoffice where humans set direction and AI handles the structured work. Strategy, tasks, and team knowledge in one brain every AI your team uses can read and update."
  page="about"
>
  <PageHead
    kicker="About"
    heading="The backoffice<br/>your AI has been missing."
    lede="Octopad is where your strategy, tasks, and team knowledge live together. One structured environment every AI your team uses (Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor) can read, update, and run the work from."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <Pillar>
        <Fragment slot="copy">
          <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-green">Our vision</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">A future where humans and AI work together, naturally.</h2>
        </Fragment>
        <div>
          <p class="copy">
            The next decade of work is not about replacing humans with agents. It's about humans and AI sharing the same workspace, the same context, and the same source of truth, so each does what it does best.
          </p>
          <p class="copy" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            The honest truth is that AI today is not strong enough to do impactful work on its own. Teams betting on full autonomy keep getting burned. What actually works is symbiosis.
          </p>
          <p class="copy" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            You set direction and make the calls. Your AI handles the structured work: pulling context, drafting plans, capturing decisions, keeping state current. Both of you contribute to the same shared brain.
          </p>
          <p class="copy" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            That is the future we're building toward. Agent delegation, when it matures, will extend this foundation, not replace the humans at the center of it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Pillar>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <Pillar reverse>
        <Fragment slot="copy">
          <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-green">Our mission</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Build the backoffice where humans and AI work together as partners.</h2>
        </Fragment>
        <div>
          <p class="copy">
            We connect strategy, tasks, and team knowledge into one structured environment every AI your team uses can read and update. You set direction. Your AI handles the structured work. Both contribute to the same source of truth.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Pillar>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <Pillar>
        <Fragment slot="copy">
          <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-green">Where we're going</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Where we're going.</h2>
        </Fragment>
        <div>
          <p class="copy">
            Right now, our focus is nailing the fundamentals of the AI back office. Context that flows, plans that hold across sessions, a shared brain that stays current as work happens. Get those three right, and everything else gets easier.
          </p>
          <p class="copy" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            Next, we're integrating autonomous agents into the middle of the system, so the back office gets smarter and more proactive on its own. Noticing slipping deadlines, flagging stale decisions, keeping plans current without a human pushing every button.
          </p>
          <p class="copy" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            We're also experimenting with agent delegation. The idea is simple: you brainstorm a full plan with an AI (code or business, either works), then hand the individual steps off to specialized agents. Each one picks up with the back office context already loaded, runs its part at the highest degree of efficiency, and reports back into the same shared brain. You keep the strategy and the final call. Agents run the structured work underneath. You gain real time back, and you ship with a high degree of confidence in what lands.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Pillar>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand
    heading="Try the backoffice your AI has been missing."
    description="Free to start. No credit card. Connect your AI in minutes."
  >
    <a href="https://www.octopad.app/signup" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Create your workspace</a>
  </CTABand>
</BaseLayout>
